----------------------------------------------------------

Welcome back to The Daily Courant, your afternoon survey of the best new re=
porting at
Puck.

=C2=A0

First up today, Eriq Gardner digs into a scandalous Hollywood breakup=E2=80=
=94no, not Baldonigate=E2=80=94between John P. Middleton, scion of a tobacc=
o empire and part-owner of the Philadelphia Phillies, and The Departed prod=
ucer Roy Lee. With a $1.5 million unpaid bill to a crisis P.R. firm and a H=
ollywood Hills mansion turned into a squatter=E2=80=99s paradise,
the whole saga invites the question: How much does celebrity media warfare =
actually cost in 2025?

Plus, below the fold: Sarah Shapiro determines whether ascendant shoe brand=
 Larroud=C3=A9 cracked the code to big retail. John Heilemann reunites with=
 comms strategist Jennifer Palmieri to circle the key players in the Dems=
=E2=80=99 Trump resistance (such as it is=E2=80=A6). And Marion Maneker ass=
esses whether
Giorgio Morandi=E2=80=99s auction prices will zoom after a new show at Davi=
d Zwirner.=C2=A0

Meanwhile, on the pods: Matt Belloni hosts legendary music executive Irving=
 Azoff on The Town to preview a massive benefit concert for L.A. fire victi=
ms. On Somebody=E2=80=99s Gotta Win, Tara Palmeri conscripts a pair of cryp=
to experts to discuss Trump=E2=80=99s geopolitical vision for digital
currency. On The Varsity, NFL Network analyst Peter Schrager joins John Our=
and to assess the NFL=E2=80=99s popularity. And on The Powers That Be, Eriq=
 connects with Peter Hamby to preview what antitrust enforcement will look =
like under Trump II.

